Enumeration Type Documentation

enum Nitobi::CalendarMode

Enumerator:
Standard  Displays the text field to type in a date and the button to drop down the calendar to pick a date.

TextFieldOnly  Displays only the text field, which will not allow the user to pick a date in the calendar but will still use the display masks and date validation of the calendar control.

CalendarOnly  Displays the calendar control directly, and the user will not be able to type in a date. The calendar is always displayed and doesnt drop down with a button.

enum Nitobi::LiveScrollingModeType

If the paging mode is LiveScrolling, this describes how it performs that operation.

Enumerator:
NotSpecified 
Peek  The grid pings the server in a binary search pattern looking for the last row.

Leap  The grid doubles its assumption of the last row every time the user scrolls to the end of the visible rows.

Once the end of the dataset is passed, it starts a binary search backwards.

enum Nitobi::UpdateAction

If a row in a datasource was modified, this enum is used to indicate what type of action was performed.

Enumerator:
Insert  The row was inserted.

Update  The row was updated.

Delete  The row was deleted.

None  No effect - the calendar just appears and disappears.

No action was taken on the row.
